snippet.textDisplay: Virus’s are extremely complex. Thank you for breaking this process down and making it very easy to understand the basics. If people really understood how complicated of a system that virus’s are, maybe they would have all  thought before they wanted to go about their days like there was not a global pandemic on earth.  The more the virus spreads, the more likely it is that it will mutate and be harder to manage.  Well, at least the more it will spread.  Anyways.  I wish I wish I wish.:. Unfortunately it seems the virus is going to go through the entire human  population on earth as well as other animals.  I saw an article saying someone’s dog was positive? Is that true? Anyways- good luck to the world

snippet.textDisplay: That god thing wasnt true, its very selective to humans especially now. An interesting thing about viruses is one that kills is a bad at being a virus. The goal of a virus is to form as many replicas as possible, and killing hosts is a set back.
